\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f4\kerning0\insrsid12191759 \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 Common Tools }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \f4\kerning0\insrsid12191759 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/winding/GridWindingGeometry.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file is the geometry backbone for grid winding. It defines triangle cache formats, boundary link helpers, and\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
 utilities like computeFaceEpsilon. If you need to alter how link intersection tolerances are computed or how triangle caches are generated, this is the file to study first.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file is used by both CPU and GPU boundary processing code. Any change here will affect classification and Q processing across platforms, so updates should be accompanied by diagnostics testing on both CPU and GPU runs.

\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/winding/GridWindingKdTree.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file provides kd tree support for triangle meshes. \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
It includes builders and query helpers used to accelerate boundary link processing. Use it when you need to speed up intersection tests or add new spatial queries to the pipeline.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
The kd tree helpers integrate with both CPU and GPU boundary processors. If you modify the kd tree interface, check all call sites in both platforms. Performance impacts are often visible in subgrid distance computation time.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/winding/GridWindingSolidMarker.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file implements the fast winding classification. The template function markSolidsWithFastWinding builds the triangle soup, initializes libigl fast winding, and evaluates winding values for each candidate node. The acces
\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 sor abstraction lets it work with CPU and GPU grid data structures.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
When tuning classification behavior such as threshold or tolerance handling, this is the file to modify. It also shows how to build and pass mesh arrays to libigl, which is helpful if you plan to replace or augment the winding evaluation.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/winding/GridWindingDiagnostics.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file defines MissingLinkCollection, QLineCollection, and WindingFieldCollection. It also provides collectMissingLinks, buildQLineCollecti\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
on, and write functions for diagnostics output. These helpers are used by both CPU and GPU diagnostics.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 BoundaryProcessingConfig lives here. It holds write flags and the fastWindingThreshold default. If you want to change output defaults or add a new diagnostic flag, this is the place to do it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f4\kerning0\insrsid12191759 \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 CPU Core }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \f4\kerning0\insrsid12191759 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/cpu/core/CMakeLists.txt
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file controls CPU build time enablement of fast winding. It sets VF_FAST_WINDING_ROOT, includes the fast winding headers, and defines VF_HAS_FAST_WINDING as a public\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
 compile definition. This is why CPU apps typically see the macro when they link cpu_core.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 Any changes here affect all CPU targets. If you want to restrict fast winding to specific apps, you would change this file and then add explicit defines at the app level.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/cpu/core/Interactors/D3Q27GridWindingInteractor.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This header declares the CPU interactor that drives grid winding boundary processing. It defines processBoundaryData and the classification helper markSolidsWithFastWinding for CPU grids. \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
It is the public interface for CPU boundary processing logic.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
When integrating fast winding into a simulation step, this interactor is the correct entry point. It keeps the boundary processing logic in one place and ensures consistent use of classification and subgrid distance computation.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/cpu/core/Interactors/D3Q27GridWindingInteractor.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
This file implements CPU boundary processing in detail. It calls markSolidsWithFastWinding when VF_HAS_FAST_WINDING is defined, then computes subgrid distances, the Q values, with computeSubgridDistancesStandalone. It also gathers missing link and Q line 
\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 diagnostics.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
This is the core CPU fast winding implementation. When debugging classification or subgrid distance computation, inspect this file for control flow, logging, and parameter use. It also contains safety checks and error messages for missing fast
\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4  winding support.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/cpu/core/SimulationObservers/GridWindingDiagnosticsSimulationObserver.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This header declares the diagnostics observer. It defines constructors that accept grid, surface, BCSet, boundary adapters, and configuration. It provides accessors for diagnostics collections.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 Use this observer when you want a self contained diagnostics run that includes classification, subgrid distance computation, and output writing. It is designed for a one time run per simulation setup.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/cpu/\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 core/SimulationObservers/GridWindingDiagnosticsSimulationObserver.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
This file implements the diagnostics observer workflow. It calls processBoundaryData, stores the results, enriches missing links, computes winding fields, and writes outputs. It also manages output directory creation and logging.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 It is the most complete CPU path for fast winding diagnostics. Changes here affect how diagnostics are orchestrated and written, but should not change the underlying classification or Q logic.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: tests/unit-\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 tests/cpu/core/GridWindingDiagnosticsSimulationObserverTest.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This test file exercises the diagnostics observer and validates behavior when fast winding is enabled. It provides baseline coverage for missing link and winding field outputs.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 Use this test when changing diagnostics output logic or when modifying the observer behavior. It provides quick feedback on whether the pipeline still produces expected results.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f4\kerning0\insrsid12191759 \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 GPU Grid Generator }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \f4\kerning0\insrsid12191759 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/CMakeLists.txt
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file controls GPU build\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
 time enablement of fast winding. It sets VF_FAST_WINDING_ROOT and defines VF_HAS_FAST_WINDING for the GridGenerator target. It also adds the necessary include paths for libigl.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 If you need to adjust how the GPU build locates fast winding headers or to change warning handling, this is the file to edit. Any change here affects all GPU grid generation targets.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/grid/GridFactory.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file selects the grid discretization strategy. When fast winding is enabled it chooses FastWindingDiscretizationStrategy. This is the first point where the GPU pipeline decides to use winding based classification.

\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 If you add a new strategy or modify the conditions under which fast winding is selected, update this file and verify that the builder follows the correct path.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/grid/GridBuilder/MultipleGridBuilder.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file implements the GPU grid builder and contains the fas\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
t winding path. It gathers winding surfaces, builds triangle caches, computes combined winding fields, and triggers classification in GridImp.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
It also coordinates boundary processing for Q values, the subgrid distances, and missing links. If you need to change how the GPU pipeline sequences classification and subgrid distance computation, this is the main file to inspect.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/grid/GridImp.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This header declares grid operations such as classifyUsingWinding. It defines interfaces for\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4  applying winding fields and for filling missing Q values.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 GridImp is the core GPU grid data structure. Any changes to how classification is applied or how fields are stored should be reflected here.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/grid/GridImp.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file implements classifyUsingWinding and related grid operations. It uses the winding field to set node types and to adjust boundary data. It is the GPU equivalent of the CPU classification application step.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 When debugging GPU classification results, this fil\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 e is essential. It also contains logic for filling missing Q values along solid neighbors.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/geometries/TriangularMesh/TriangularMeshStrategy.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This header declares the triangular mesh strategy used by the grid generator. It integrates mesh handling with the discretization strategy selection, including fast winding when enabled.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 If you need to add mesh preprocessing steps or change how meshes are presented to the grid builder, this file is the correct entry point.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/geometries/TriangularMesh/TriangularMeshStrategy.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file implements the triangular mesh strategy. It prepares mesh data, selects winding surfaces, and hands the data to the grid builder. It is where mesh level decisions are mapped to grid generation actions.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file is important for aligning GPU mesh handling with CPU behavior. If meshes are treated differently across platforms, classification results will diverge.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/utilities/GridWindingSolidM\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 arkerGpu.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file provides a GPU grid accessor that reuses the common fast winding marker logic. It adapts GPU grid node storage to the accessor interface expected by GridWindingSolidMarker.h.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 If you need to adjust how GPU nodes are iterated or how solid flags are applied during classification, this is the adapter to update.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/utilities/GridWindingBoundaryGpuCore.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file implements GPU boundary processing utilities. It builds triangle caches, processes boundary links, and \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 
supports missing link collection. It provides the GPU side of subgrid distance computation and boundary analysis.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 The routines here are performance sensitive. Any changes should be profiled because this code runs across the entire grid during generation or diagnostics.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/io/GridWindingDiagnosticsGpu.h
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This header declares GPU diagnostics output helpers. It exposes functions to write missing links, Q lines, and winding fields for GPU grids.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 Use this file to understand the interfa\hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 ce for GPU diagnostics and to add new diagnostics outputs if needed.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 File: src/gpu/GridGenerator/io/GridWindingDiagnosticsGpu.cpp
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 This file implements GPU diagnostics output. It computes winding fields for visualization, writes missing links and Q lines, and integrates with the common diagnostics collections.
\par 
\par \hich\af4\dbch\af31505\loch\f4 When adjusting output formats or adding new diagnostic data for GPU runs, this is the implementation file to update.
\par 
